Phase 2 — Persistence & Items:
    - Item types (potions, swords, armor, scrolls)
    - Pick up items from the map
    - Inventory system (equip slots + 10-slot backpack)
    - Item effects (heal, teleport, reveal map, stat boosts)
    - Multiple floors with stairs (procedural generation per floor)
    - Enemy scaling per floor (new types: Ogres, Dragons)
    - Save game to JSON file
    - Load game from file (resume exactly)
    - Config file for keybindings/preferences
    - CLI arguments (--new, --load, --seed)

Phase 3 — Procedural Generation & Algorithms:
    - BSP dungeon generation
    - BFS/DFS to verify all rooms are reachable
    - A* pathfinding for enemy AI
    - Weighted loot tables (common → legendary)
    - Shadowcasting field of view
    - Mini-map of explored areas
    - Scrollable combat log
    - Status effects (poison, stun, haste)
    - Generics for typed containers / loot tables
    - Profile and optimize hot loops

Phase 4 — Multiplayer & Networking:
    - HTTP REST API server (POST /runs, GET /leaderboard)
    - Client-side score submission after death
    - Display leaderboard from main menu
    - Input validation and rate limiting
    - Co-op mode via TCP/WebSocket (stretch goal)
    - Shared map, independent inventories
    - Turn synchronization for two players
    - Handle disconnects gracefully

Phase 5 — Polish & Engineering:
    - Unit tests (combat, loot tables, pathfinding, serialization)
    - Integration tests for the API
    - Property-based tests (every generated map is solvable)
    - CI pipeline (lint, test, build on push)
    - Structured logging
    - README with build instructions + screenshots
    - Package and distribute (binary, Docker, or package registry)
    - Plugin/mod system (stretch goal)
